{"TopicId":187667,"ForumId":16,"TopicTitle":"AN DN nodes for current orbit disappeared","CreatedByName":"Dizor","CreatedById":161502,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-08-25T17:15:06Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"Dizor","CreatedById":161502,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-08-25T17:15:06Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nFor example, I am on the way from Kerbin to Eve, Eve is selected as target, and i want to create a maneuver node on \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Descending Node\u0022\u003EDN\u003C/abbr\u003E node of current orbit. But game does not show where \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Ascending Node\u0022\u003EAN\u003C/abbr\u003E/\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Descending Node\u0022\u003EDN\u003C/abbr\u003E nodes are. It displays \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Ascending Node\u0022\u003EAN\u003C/abbr\u003E/\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Descending Node\u0022\u003EDN\u003C/abbr\u003E nodes for future conics instead:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u00222JBgJy.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 data-ratio=\u002261.85\u0022 height=\u0022633\u0022 width=\u00221024\u0022 src=\u0022https://i.vgy.me/2JBgJy.png\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHow do i activate displaying \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Ascending Node\u0022\u003EAN\u003C/abbr\u003E/\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Descending Node\u0022\u003EDN\u003C/abbr\u003E nodes for all patched conics?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Empiro","CreatedById":112072,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-08-25T17:19:54Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nTry just placing a maneuver node where you think it should be? I think it will force it to show the nodes for the current orbit.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Dizor","CreatedById":161502,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-08-25T19:38:10Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223659478\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022187667\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221566753594\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022112072\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Empiro\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n2 hours ago, Empiro said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI think it will force it to show the nodes for the current orbit\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNo it not.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nMy \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Descending Node\u0022\u003EDN\u003C/abbr\u003E location assumption was wrong a little (by few centimeters)\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u002288aYxn.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 data-ratio=\u002252.92\u0022 height=\u0022417\u0022 width=\u0022788\u0022 src=\u0022https://i.vgy.me/88aYxn.png\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI limited patched conics in game options to 2 and got a correct marker. But this way is very inconvenient.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"mikegarrison","CreatedById":137807,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-08-25T19:56:44Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe game seems to always place the nodes according to your final \u0022conic\u0022. Sadly for you, you have that planetary intercept messing you up.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nDo it by hand. Go to map mode, rotate the map until you are on plane and then find the intercept point.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOr use mechjeb.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOr limit the number of conics until you get the one you want, like you did.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222019-08-25T19:58:05Z\u0022 title=\u002208/25/2019 07:58  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00224 yr\u0022\u003EAugust 25, 2019\u003C/time\u003E by mikegarrison\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"FloppyRocket","CreatedById":173990,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-08-27T23:40:27Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe game does its best to tell you what it thinks you want to know.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt isn\u0027t always right.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}